Control file for Drift self-improvement loop.
Check this file before every cycle.

Current status: RUNNING
Direction: Firstly look at the commit history and focus on functionality added recently to hunt for bugs and inconsistency first - that's where more bugs happen, write more test cases if something is missing. look at commit and bug history to figure out what kind of bugs and request mostly come from and try to learn the taste of the app as well. Continue to research on UX for how to improve food and exercise logging and implement. Enrich food and exercise database, make it really good. General directions on how to make UI really good read research papges on it. Ensure food database matches accuate calories, macros and fiber. Other things - Research but don't implement yet - curate ideas that human can read later, 1) how to help people with images or vidoes on how to do these exercises. 2) How to use AI so people have to do less form filling

Status options:
- RUNNING: continue the loop
- STOP: finish current work, commit, halt
- PAUSE: commit and wait for instructions
- REDIRECT: read Direction field, apply changes, set back to RUNNING

To give feedback during a session, change status to REDIRECT and write in Direction.
Examples:
- "Focus only on bug fixes for the next hour"
- "Add personality: accessibility reviewer"
- "Revert the last color change"
- "Skip lab biomarker work"
